FIRST INSTALL

1.- install virtualenv (pip install virtualenv)

2.- activate virtual env in your project

    a.- python3 -m virtualenv bin (this command generates a bin folder with python references)

    b.- activating virtualenv

        a.- bin\Scripts\activate (on cmd windows)

        b.- source bin/Scripts/activate (on git bash or linux shell)

    c.- when you activate the virtualenv you must see a prefix on your shell, the name of the prefix will be "(bin)"

    d.- if you need closing the virtualenv you type "deactive" and press enter on the shell

3.- install requirements (pip install -r requirements.txt)

4.- if you have an error like a "'config-win.h': No such file or directory",
    you need to install the mysql C connector from this link https://dev.mysql.com/downloads/file/?id=378015

5.- to deploying statics files execute "python3 manage.py collectstatic"